The Bongani Mountain Lodge, situated in the Mthethomusha Game Reserve on the southern border of the Kruger National Park, has burned down. This has been confirmed by MTPA spokesperson Kholofelo Nkambule. Nkambule said they are still awaiting a report from the owners that will give more details on the extent of the damage and that an investigation will be lodged. ALSO READ: Weather service issues level-5 rain warning for Mbombela This is a developing story and more information will follow.